        "title": "Argo marine floats vertical profiles",
        "description": "Argo is an international program to observe the interior of the ocean with a fleet of profiling floats drifting in the deep ocean currents (https://argo.ucsd.edu). Argo GDAC is a dataset of 10 billion in situ ocean observations from 20 000 profiling floats (4.000 active) which started 25 years ago. Argo GDAC is a collection of 3 million NetCDF files. It is a major asset for ocean and climate science, a contributor to IOCCP reports. Argo data are available with a one click download https://doi.org/10.17882/42182",
